-18T14:12:40.063Z\",\n  \"specId\": \"011\",\n  \"folderSlug\": \"sk-design-styles-utilization\",","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/description.json","text":"{\n  \"level\": \"2\",\n  \"specFolder\": \"sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization\",\n  \"description\": \"Packet `010-sk-design-styles-from-refero` extracts ~1,290 real design systems into `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/`, each a folder of DESIGN.md +\",\n  \"keywords\": [\n    \"packet\",\n    \"010-sk-design-styles-from-refero\",\n    \"extracts\",\n    \"real\",\n    \"design\",\n    \"systems\",\n    \"opencode\",\n    \"skills\",\n    \"sk-design\",\n    \"styles\",\n    \"folder\"\n  ],\n  \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-07-18T14:12:40.063Z\",\n  \"specId\": \"011\",\n  \"folderSlug\": \"sk-design-styles-utilization\",\n  \"parentChain\": [\n    \"sk-design\"\n  ],\n  \"memorySequence\": 0,\n  \"memoryNameHistory\": []\n}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":26,"totalLines":26,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/description.json","time":{"start":1784385808504,"end":1784385808515}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0874244a11d8ffaa016a5b91104ee081918c2c246d1d31a36d"}},"id":"prt_f75aea8680015smMjieMKwkNt3","sessionID":"ses_08a55b97affezjS590Sxu4oUZ9","messageID":"msg_f75ae4758001uq5s9VHYJ4sBNB"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784385808548,"sessionID":"ses_08a55b97affezjS590Sxu4oUZ9","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_T1xca5qb21rDIkihLwcEfRkJ","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"`?\\.opencode/[^`\\s)]+|\\.opencode/[^\\s)]+","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization","include":"{spec,plan,tasks,checklist,implementation-summary}.md"},"output":"Found 63 matches\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/004-retrieval-substrate/spec.md:\n  Line 43: This phase builds the shared retrieval substrate for the 1,290-bundle styles library at `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/` — the foundation the completed research (`../001-research-utilization/research/lineages/sol/research.md`, §4, §5, §9, §15 Phase A) ranked first (leverage 5, cost 5-8 days, reversibility 5). It delivers a committed, checked retrieval manifest; deterministic eligibility applied before any ranking; a disposable, same-generation SQLite FTS5/BM25 projection; compact candidate cards; generation-guarded hydration; and a blocking `CORPUS_USE_PROOF v1` gate. Every downstream phase in packet 011 (md-generator schema contract, global-mode consumption, guardrails) consumes this substrate, so it is authored and built first.\n\n  Line 74: Packet `010-sk-design-styles-from-refero` extracted 1,290 real design-system bundles into `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/` (1,291 child directories, one of which is `_harness` infrastructure). Nothing in the `sk-design` runtime consumes that corpus: there is no committed index, no eligibility discipline, no ranking, and no proof gate. Ad-hoc grep over 20.38 MB of `DESIGN.md` is unjoinable and unstable, loading the whole corpus is ~85 MB of context and a copy-exposure hazard, and a hand-maintained index drifts (the corpus moved from 974 to 1,290 bundles during research while `styles/README.md` stayed at 50). Without a generation-bound substrate, every downstream utilization phase would reinvent retrieval and risk stale, un-provenanced, or averaged output.\n\n  Line 104: | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/style-library.mjs` | Create (NEW/proposed) | CLI entrypoint: `build --write`, `build --check`, `query`, `hydrate` |\n\n  Line 105: | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/manifest.mjs` | Create (NEW/proposed) | Manifest schema, refresh algorithm, content/generation hashing |\n\n  Line 106: | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/eligibility.mjs` | Create (NEW/proposed) | Required-facet, exclusion, and provenance/rights gates (pre-ranking) |\n\n  Line 107: | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/rank-fts.mjs` | Create (NEW/proposed) | Disposable same-generation SQLite FTS5/BM25 projection + source-scan fallback |\n\n  Line 108: | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/cards.mjs` | Create (NEW/proposed) | Compact candidate-card assembly and byte-capping |\n\n  Line 109: | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/hydrate.mjs` | Create (NEW/proposed) | Generation-guarded hydration of permitted artifacts/slices |\n\n  Line 110: | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/corpus-use-proof.mjs` | Create (NEW/proposed) | `CORPUS_USE_PROOF v1` schema + validator |\n\n  Line 111: | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_retrieval-manifest.json` | Create (NEW/proposed) | The only committed retrieval artifact (byte-stable generated output) |\n\n  Line 112: | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/__tests__/**` | Create (NEW/proposed) | Change/invalidation, fallback, generation-mismatch, and proof-card fixtures |\n\n  Line 280: - **Source corpus**: `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/001-research-utilization/spec.md:\n  Line 61: The extracted styles library (`.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/`, ~1,290 real design systems as DESIGN.md + token files) is unused by the sk-design runtime. Before building anything, the smart ways to exploit it — and the traps — must be established with evidence rather than guessed.\n\n  Line 143: - **Source corpus**: `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/006-md-generator-study-exemplars/spec.md:\n  Line 215: - **Subject backend**: `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/005-md-generator-schema-contract/spec.md:\n  Line 266: - **Subject backend**: `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/spec.md:\n  Line 61: The sk-design `design-md-generator` mode (backend `formatters-v3` + the DESIGN.md section schema at `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/`) generates design documents without any grounding in real, high-quality design systems. The 1,290-style library is exactly that grounding — 1,290 hand-shipped DESIGN.md + token bundles — but nothing connects the two. The 001 research established a retrieval substrate; this phase asks the narrower, deeper question of how that corpus should actually improve md-generator output.\n\n  Line 145: - **Subject backend**: `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/`\n\n  Line 146: - **Source corpus**: `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/spec.md:\n  Line 61: Packet `010-sk-design-styles-from-refero` extracts ~1,290 real design systems into `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/`, each a folder of DESIGN.md + CSS-variables + Tailwind-v4 + design-tokens + provenance. That is a large, high-value corpus, but nothing in the `sk-design` runtime yet consumes it: the hub and its nested modes (interface, foundations, motion, audit, md-generator) have no retrieval, indexing, or reference discipline for the library, so its leverage is currently zero and its size is a liability rather than an asset.\n\n  Line 90: | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/**` | Modify | 002+ (planned) | Utilization features the research seeds (retrieval, mode consumption, guardrails) |\n\n  Line 142: - **Source corpus**: `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/` (the extracted library; packet `010-sk-design-styles-from-refero`).\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/009-foundations-motion/spec.md:\n  Line 103: | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/**` | Create (proposed) | Relationship blueprint, typed compatibility graph, transformation ledger, `not-assessed` checks. |\n\n  Line 104: | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/**` | Create (proposed) | Restraint gate, polarity-aware eligibility, purpose/state archetypes, negative baselines. |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/008-interface-audit-pilots/spec.md:\n  Line 104: | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/**` | Modify (proposed) | Wire the phase-007 seam: anchor + bounded contrast retrieval, relational exemplar, decision-only handoff. |\n\n  Line 105: | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/**` | Modify (proposed) | Wire the comparison lane: non-authoritative refs, drift fixtures, evidence labels. |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/004-retrieval-substrate/tasks.md:\n  Line 131: - [ ] T028 Add CI selectors on `styles/**`, the engine, and mode contracts (`.opencode/skill