of 10 iterations.\n27: - Pause sentinel or unrecoverable state corruption.\n28: \n29: ## 6. COMPLETED DIMENSIONS\n30: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n31: - D1 Correctness — iteration 001 — score 78/100; parent/child lifecycle inventory and current-runtime reconciliation completed.\n32: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n33: \n34: ## 7. RUNNING FINDINGS\n35: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n36: - P0: 0 active\n37: - P1: 1 active\n38: - P2: 0 active\n39: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n40: \n41: ## 8. WHAT WORKED\n42: - Iteration 001: Direct parent reads plus exact lifecycle/status searches across all configured child evidence isolated the stale continuity class without broadening into style-corpus review.\n43: - Iteration 001: Exact sk-design contract searches confirmed that planned packet-011 retrieval/proof fields are not falsely represented as live runtime behavior.\n44: \n45: ## 9. WHAT FAILED\n46: - Spec Kit Memory context retrieval timed out twice before initialization; continue from direct repository evidence only.\n47: - Iteration 001: Structural-impact analysis was unavailable by prompt-pack design for the detached lineage; graphless direct evidence was used instead.\n48: \n49: ## 10. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n50: - Memory-context retrieval for initialization is exhausted for this lineage after two timeouts.\n51: \n52: ## 10A. SATURATED / SWEPT DIMENSIONS AND EXPANSION FRONTIER\n53: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n54: - Completed pivots: 1\n55: - Failed pivots: 0\n56: - Audited overrides: 0\n57: - Swept: correctness lifecycle/status inventory\n58: - Pivot lineage: iteration 001 correctness inventory -> security trust-boundary review\n59: - Remaining frontier: security, traceability, maintainability\n60: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n61: \n62: ## 11. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n63: - Full style-corpus content audit: outside the declared packet-level review and not required to test the utilization contracts.\n64: \n65: ## 12. NEXT FOCUS\n66: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -