ap coverage gate.\n\n## 3. REVIEW DIMENSIONS (remaining)\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- [x] D1 Correctness — iteration 001, 78/100 (one P1 lifecycle-consistency defect)\n- [ ] D2 Security\n- [ ] D3 Traceability\n- [ ] D4 Maintainability\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n## 4. NON-GOALS\n- Do not implement any planned retrieval or mode-consumption feature.\n- Do not mutate the packet or sk-design runtime under review.\n- Do not audit the content quality of all 1,290 style bundles individually.\n\n## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n- Legal convergence after all four dimensions and both core traceability protocols have coverage and stabilization.\n- Hard ceiling of 10 iterations.\n- Pause sentinel or unrecoverable state corruption.\n\n## 6. COMPLETED DIMENSIONS\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- D1 Correctness — iteration 001 — score 78/100; parent/child lifecycle inventory and current-runtime reconciliation completed.\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n## 7. RUNNING FINDINGS\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- P0: 0 active\n- P1: 1 active\n- P2: 0 active\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n## 8. WHAT WORKED\n- Iteration 001: Direct parent reads plus exact lifecycle/status searches across all configured child evidence isolated the stale continuity class without broadening into style-corpus review.\n- Iteration 001: Exact sk-design contract searches confirmed that planned packet-011 retrieval/proof fields are not falsely represented as live runtime behavior.\n\n## 9. WHAT FAILED\n- Spec Kit Memory context retrieval timed out twice before initialization; continue from direct repository evidence only.\n- Iteration 001: Structural-impact analysis was unavailable by prompt-pack design for the detached lineage; graphless direct evidence was used instead.\n\n## 10. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n- Memory-context retrieval for initialization is exhausted for this lineage after two timeouts.\n\n## 10A. SATURATED / SWEPT DIMENSIONS AND EXPANSION FRONTIER\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- Completed pivots: 1\n- Failed pivots: 0\n- Audited overrides: 0\n- Swept: correctness lifecycle/status inventory\n- Pivot lineage: iteration 001 correctness inventory -> security trust-boundary review\n- Remaining frontier: security, traceability, maintainability\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n## 11. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n- Full style-corpus content audit: outside the declared packet-level review and not required to test the utilization contracts.\n\n## 12. NEXT FOCUS\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- dimension: security\n- focus area: corpus retrieval, rights/provenance, injection, path handling, and Open Design transport trust boundaries\n- reason: correctness coverage is complete and planned phases 004/006/007/010 introduce security-sensitive boundaries\n- rotation status: correctness complete; rotate to security\n- blocked/productive carry-forward: direct reads and exact searches productive; graph tooling blocked by detached-lineage containment\n- required evidence: security requirements in phases 004/006/007/010 and exact current transport/runtime guardrails\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n## 13. KNOWN CONTEXT\n### Bounded Context Snapshot\n- Target pointers: parent `spec.md`, `description.json`, `graph-metadata.json`; ten child packet specs and evidence docs; sk-design hub registry and six mode contracts.\n- Behavior claims: research phases 001-003 are complete; phases 004-010 are planned; current runtime does not yet consume the extracted styles library.\n- Reuse and conventions: lean phase-parent trio, child-owned implementation evidence, sk-design mode registry routing.\n- Review risks and gaps: parent metadata may lag child state; planned child scaffolds may use completion-looking artifacts; memory context was unavailable; no root resource map exists.\n- Unresolved carry-forward: parent plus phase-002/003 spec continuity fields conflict with their recorded completed states (iteration 001 P1).\n- Out of scope: source-style extraction correctness and individual style bundle quality.\n\n## 14. CROSS-REFERENCE STATUS\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n| Protocol | Level | Status | Iteration | Notes |\n|----------|-------|--------|-----------|-------|\n| `spec_code` | core | covered | 001 | Current runtime lacks planned packet-011 retrieval/proof fields, consistent with implementation phases remaining planned. |\n| `checklist_evidence` | core | covered | 001 | Planned phases 004-010 have no checked completion evidence; completed phases 001-003 have implementation summaries, with stale spec continuity in 002/003 recorded as P1. |\n| `skill_agent` | overlay | notApplicable | - | Target is a spec folder. |\n| `agent_cross_runtime` | overlay | notApplicable | - | Target is a spec folder. |\n| `feature_catalog_code` | overlay | notApplicable | 001 | No feature-catalog claim exists in configured packet evidence. |\n| `playbook_capability` | overlay | notApplicable | 001 | No playbook or executable-scenario claim exists in configured packet evidence. |\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n## 15. FILES UNDER REVIEW\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n| File group | Dimensions Reviewed | Last Iteration | Findings | Status |\n|------------|---------------------|----------------|----------|--------|\n| Parent lean trio | correctness | 001 | 1 | reviewed; stale continuity participates in P1 |\n| Child packets 001-010 | correctness | 001 | 1 | reviewed; phase-002/003 stale continuity participates in P1 |\n| sk-design hub and mode contracts | correctness | 001 | 0 | reviewed; current planned-vs-live boundary confirmed |\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n## 16. REVIEW BOUNDARIES\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- Max iterations: 10\n- Convergence threshold: 0.1\n- Stop policy: convergence\n- Rolling STOP threshold: 0.08\n- No-progress threshold: 0.05\n- Coverage stabilization passes required: 1\n- Session lineage: sessionId=fanout-sol-a-1784385520599-ecg4bg, parentSessionId=null, generation=1, lineageMode=new\n- Findings registry: `deep-review-findings-re