iteria.\"}},{\"id\":\"SOL-A-I002-P1-002\",\"severity\":\"P1\",\"category\":\"security\",\"title\":\"The STUDY injection envelope records a boundary but does not neutralize untrusted instructions\",\"file\":\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/006-md-generator-study-exemplars/spec.md:104-117\",\"evidence\":\"The planned transformer injects corpus-derived observations but specifies only an auditable envelope and literal/span leak gates, not instruction rejection or a data-only prompt boundary.\",\"findingClass\":\"cross-consumer\",\"scopeProof\":\"Scoped search found envelope references across phase-006 artifacts but no behavioral prompt-injection criterion; phase-007 authority ordering does not sanitize prompt content.\",\"affectedSurfaceHints\":[\"study transformer\",\"STUDY prompt block\",\"adversarial fixtures\",\"runGuided retry\"],\"content_hash\":\"5d2be1beddf22032bde4e59d4bb0d4b73c7f3a54d1718ede78e6988f0c7918aa\",\"claimAdjudication\":{\"type\":\"claim-adjudication\",\"findingId\":\"SOL-A-I002-P1-002\",\"claim\":\"Corpus-borne instructions can influence generated prose while all planned phase-006 controls pass because the leak gate only tests copied values and spans.\",\"evidenceRefs\":[\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/006-md-generator-study-exemplars/spec.md:73-79\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/006-md-generator-study-exemplars/spec.md:104-117\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/006-md-generator-study-exemplars/spec.md:165-187\"],\"counterevidenceSought\":\"Searched assigned phase trees for prompt injection, untrusted content, instruction rejection, sanitization, and boundary controls; reviewed de-literalization, locked FACTS, authority order, leak gates, and retry.\",\"alternativeExplanation\":\"A strict transformer could incidentally remove imperative text, but that behavior is neither specified nor tested.\",\"finalSeverity\":\"P1\",\"confidence\":