{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784389911774,"sessionID":"ses_08a55b97affezjS590Sxu4oUZ9","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_sAQliaIGxUUqOgo6DGQm8E9x","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/review/lineages/sol-a/iterations/iteration-005.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/review/lineages/sol-a/iterations/iteration-005.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deep Review Iteration 005\n2: \n3: ## Dispatcher\n4: - Route: `mode=review`, `target_agent=deep-review`, single YAML-owned LEAF iteration\n5: - Focus: cross-dimension stabilization and adversarial replay of all five authoritative P1 claims\n6: - Budget profile: `verify` (graphless direct-read, counterevidence, and consumer-impact replay)\n7: \n8: ## Files Reviewed\n9: - Parent `spec.md` and `graph-metadata.json`; phase-002/003 specs and implementation summaries\n10: - Phase-004 retrieval spec/tasks/checklist; phase-006 STUDY spec/tasks/checklist; phase-007 authority seam\n11: - Phase-005–010 dependency declarations and child graph metadata\n12: - Phase-009/010 specs/plans plus current foundations, motion, and Open Design contracts\n13: - `system-spec-kit` continuity and graph-consumer contracts as named integration evidence only\n14: \n15: ## Findings - New\n16: No new finding IDs were created. The five authoritative P1s were replayed adversarially and remain active at the same severity.\n17: \n18: ### P0 Findings\n19: None.\n20: \n21: ### P1 Findings\n22: 1. **Completed research phases retain pre-run continuity state** -- `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/spec.md:13-25` -- The parent still says to run phase 001 at 0%, while its phase map marks 001-003 complete; phase-002/003 specs still say to dispatch completed research at 10% while their implementation summaries are complete at 100%. Resume prefers child implementation-summary continuity and a phase-parent pointer/list, which contains the immediate routing impact, but `--no-redirect` and canonical-doc fallback still expose the contradictory parent/spec state. The P1 therefore remains a required canonical-state repair rather than a blocker. [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/spec.md:13-25`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/spec.md:46`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/spec.md:13-30`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/implementation-summary.md:10-30`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/003-global-modes-utilization/spec.md:13-30`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/003-global-modes-utilization/implementation-summary.md:10-31`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/quick_reference.md:492-498`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/validation/template_compliance_contract.md:264`]\n23:    - Finding class: matrix/evidence\n24:    - Scope proof: Parent and all completed-child continuity surfaces were reread; phase-parent pointer/list behavior and child implementation-summary precedence were checked as counterevidence, but neither makes the contradictory canonical metadata accurate.\n25:    - Affected surface hints: `parent coordination snapshot`, `phase-002 resume fallback`, `phase-003 resume fallback`, `canonical packet retrieval`\n26: \n27: ```json\n28: {\"type\":\"claim-adjudication\",\"findingId\":\"SOL-A-I001-P1-001\",\"claim\":\"Canonical packet surfaces give obsolete next actions and completion percentages for already-completed research phases.\",\"evidenceRefs\":[\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/spec.md:13-25\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/spec.md:46\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/spec.md:13-30\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/implementation-summary.md:10-30\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/003-global-modes-utilization/spec.md:13-30\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/003-global-modes-utilization/implementation-summary.md:10-31\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/quick_reference.md:492-498\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/validation/template_compliance_contract.md:264\"],\"counterevidenceSought\":\"Replayed child implementation-summary precedence, phase-parent pointer/list routing, null-pointer behavior, and --no-redirect canonical-doc exposure.\",\"alternativeExplanation\":\"Normal child resume consumes the complete implementation-summary continuity, and a parent resume with a null pointer lists children rather than obeying the stale parent next action; this contains immediate misrouting but does not remove contradictory canonical state or no-redirect/fallback exposure.\",\"finalSeverity\":\"P1\",\"confidence\":0.87,\"downgradeTrigger\":\"Downgrade to P2 only if every completion, indexing, no-redirect, and canonical-doc consumer is proven to suppress these spec continuity fields and the stale blocks are non-authoritative by contract.\"}\n29: ```\n30: \n31: 2. **Hydration has no contracted filesystem-containment boundary** -- `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/004-retrieval-substrate/spec.md:103-112` -- The hydration producer accepts manifest-selected artifacts and re-hashes them, but no requirement, task, checklist row, or negative fixture requires canonical-root containment, traversal rejection, or a symlink policy. Generation mismatch and rights controls are counterevidence for adjacent risks, not containment. Downstream STUDY hydration consumes this shared producer, so the missing negative boundary remains P1. [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/004-retrieval-substrate/spec.md:103-112`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/004-retrieval-substrate/spec.md:124-136`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/004-retrieval-substrate/spec.md:188-200`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/004-retrieval-substrate/tasks.md:106-112`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/004-retrieval-substrate/checklist.md:86-102`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/006-md-generator-study-exemplars/spec.md:73-79`]\n32:    - Finding class: class-of-bug\n33:    - Scope proof: Exact containment searches across the phase-004 owner found only canonical generation-input language and no realpath/traversal/symlink control; producer tasks and the security/fix matrix omit the corresponding negative tests.\n34:    - Affected surface hints: `manifest path producer`, `hydrate CLI`, `source-scan fallback`, `STUDY hydration consumer`\n35: \n36: ```json\n37: {\"type\":\"claim-adjudication\",\"findingId\":\"SOL-A-I002-P1-001\",\"claim\":\"The phase-004 contract permits a conforming implementation to hydrate a corpus path that resolves outside the styles root because no containment or symlink invariant is specified.\",\"evidenceRefs\":[\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/004-retrieval-substrate/spec.md:103-112\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/004-retrieval-substrate/spec.md:124-136\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/004-retrieval-substrate/spec.md:188-200\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/004-retrieval-substrate/tasks.md:106-112\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/004-retrieval-substrate/checklist.md:86-102\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/006-md-generator-study-exemplars/spec.md:73-79\"],\"counterevidenceSought\":\"Searched the owner requirements, tasks, checklist, edge cases, and the STUDY consumer for realpath, canonical containment, traversal, symlink, root escape, and outside-root negative fixtures.\",\"alternativeExplanation\":\"Manifest-derived paths, generation re-hashing, and a future implementation may independently constrain reads; none is a binding root-containment invariant or negative test expectation.\",\"finalSeverity\":\"P1\",\"confidence\":0.93,\"downgradeTrigger\":\"Downgrade to P2 after immutable safe manifest paths, canonical root containment, explicit symlink policy, and negative traversal/escape fixtures become binding acceptance criteria.\"}\n38: ```\n39: \n40: 3. **The STUDY injection envelope records a boundary but does not neutralize untrusted instructions** -- `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/006-md-generator-study-exemplars/spec.md:104-117` -- Phase 006 injects transformed corpus observations into the prompt and checks literal/span leakage at the authored-draft boundary, but it has no closed data-only schema, imperative/instruction rejection, or behavioral non-influence fixture. The phase-007 authority order prevents corpus evidence from becoming authority but does not sanitize the prompt content. The prompt producer and `runGuided` retry consumer can therefore pass every specified leak test while following a non-literal corpus instruction. [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/006-md-generator-study-exemplars/spec.md:73-79`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/006-md-generator-study-exemplars/spec.md:104-117`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/006-md-generator-study-exemplars/spec.md:165-187`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/006-md-generator-study-exemplars/tasks.md:65-80`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/006-md-generator-study-exemplars/checklist.md:96-118`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/007-shared-context-seam/spec.md:99-111`]\n41:    - Finding class: cross-consumer\n42:    - Scope proof: Exact prompt-injection counterevidence search found only the finding-class label; direct producer/consumer replay covered transformer, prompt builder, plan builder, authored-draft gate, retry, fixture matrix, and shared authority ordering.\n43:    - Affected surface hints: `study transformer`, `STUDY prompt block`, `buildWritePrompt/buildPlan`, `runGuided retry`, `behavioral fixtures`\n44: \n45: ```json\n46: {\"type\":\"claim-adjudication\",\"findingId\":\"SOL-A-I002-P1-002\",\"claim\":\"The planned phase-006 controls can pass while corpus-borne instructions influence generated prose, because the envelope is metadata and the leak gate only tests copied values/spans.\",\"evidenceRefs\":[\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/006-md-generator-study-exemplars/spec.md:73-79\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/006-md-generator-study-exemplars/spec.md:104-117\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/006-md-generator-study-exemplars/spec.md:165-187\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/006-md-generator-study-exemplars/tasks.md:65-80\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/006-md-generator-study-exemplars/checklist.md:96-118\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/007-shared-context-seam/spec.md:99-111\"],\"counterevidenceSought\":\"Searched requirements, tasks, checklist, fixtures, and shared authority controls for prompt injection, untrusted instructions, imperative rejection, data-only parsing, sanitization, and behavioral non-influence tests.\",\"alternativeExplanation\":\"A strict de-literalizing transformer and fixed authority order could incidentally discard imperatives, but neither requires instruction rejection and the exact/span leak signals cannot detect non-literal instruction following.\",\"finalSeverity\":\"P1\",\"confidence\":0.92,\"downgradeTrigger\":\"Downgrade to P2 if the transformer becomes a closed data-only schema with explicit instruction rejection and adversarial behavioral non-influence fixtures across prompt and draft consumers.\"}\n47: ```\n48: \n49: 4. **Canonical parent surfaces omit the implementation-phase dependency graph** -- `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/spec.md:121-126` -- The parent handoff table records only the research-to-implementation transition, while phase-005–010 docs declare blocking prerequisites and all child `manual.depends_on` arrays remain empty. The graph parser converts `depends_on` into `blocks` causal links, so empty arrays remove these edges from graph/index consumers even though child-local tasks contain human-readable blockers. Child-local controls limit immediate risk but do not give orchestration and memory consumers a canonical dependency projection. [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/spec.md:121-126`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/graph-metadata.json:6-21`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/005-md-generator-schema-contract/spec.md:143-150`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/006-md-generator-study-exemplars/tasks.md:56-70`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/007-shared-context-seam/spec.md:128-135`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/009-foundations-motion/spec.md:143-150`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/010-open-design-transport/spec.md:125-135`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/graph/graph-metadata-parser.ts:1712-1723`]\n50:    - Finding class: matrix/evidence\n51:    - Scope proof: Exact dependency replay covered the parent handoff, every phase-004–010 graph file, child-local blocking declarations, and the system graph consumer that maps `depends_on` to `blocks` links.\n52:    - Affected surface hints: `parent phase map`, `child graph metadata`, `causal graph blocks`, `resume/planning context`\n53: \n54: ```json\n55: {\"type\":\"claim-adjudication\",\"findingId\":\"SOL-A-I003-P1-001\",\"claim\":\"The canonical parent and graph metadata cannot represent or surface the implementation-phase ordering that child packets require.\",\"evidenceRefs\":[\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/spec.md:121-126\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/graph-metadata.json:6-21\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/005-md-generator-schema-contract/spec.md:143-150\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/006-md-generator-study-exemplars/tasks.md:56-70\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/007-shared-context-seam/spec.md:128-135\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/009-foundations-motion/spec.md:143-150\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/010-open-design-transport/spec.md:125-135\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/graph/graph-metadata-parser.ts:1712-1723\"],\"counterevidenceSought\":\"Reviewed child dependency tables and blocked tasks, parent transition rules, every planned-child graph field, and the graph parser for proof that child-local prose alone is the canonical machine-consumed ordering source.\",\"alternativeExplanation\":\"Child-local blocked tasks encode ordering for a human implementer and all phases remain planned; however, graph consumers map only populated manual.depends_on fields into blocks links, so the canonical machine surface still omits the relationships.\",\"finalSeverity\":\"P1\",\"confidence\":0.86,\"downgradeTrigger\":\"Downgrade to P2 if the owning workflow proves child-local blockers are the sole validated ordering authority and graph blocks are explicitly non-orchestrational/non-retrieval metadata.\"}\n56: ```\n57: \n58: 5. **Two implementation packets classify existing mode and transport surfaces as new creations** -- `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/009-foundations-motion/spec.md:99-104` -- Phase 009 labels existing foundations and motion directory globs `Create` in both spec and plan, while phase 010's spec labels its existing transport directory `Create` and its plan says `Add`. The plans, rollback text, and ADRs repeatedly say “additions,” which is substantial counterevidence against destructive replacement and prevents escalation; however, the authoritative affected-surface action labels still contradict the current owners and leave additive file boundaries unnamed. This remains a P1 spec mismatch to resolve before implementation dispatch. [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/009-foundations-motion/spec.md:99-104`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/009-foundations-motion/plan.md:97-105`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/009-foundations-motion/decision-record.md:125-131`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/010-open-design-transport/spec.md:83-88`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/010-open-design-transport/plan.md:91-97`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/010-open-design-transport/plan.md:143-146`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/SKILL.md:1-15`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/SKILL.md:1-15`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-mcp-open-design/SKILL.md:1-18`]\n59:    - Finding class: matrix/evidence\n60:    - Scope proof: Action-label search covered phase-004–010; direct reads prove all three directory owners already exist, while phase-009 ADR/plan and phase-010 plan/rollback prove intended semantics are additive but do not reconcile the owning labels.\n61:    - Affected surface hints: `design-foundations contract`, `design-motion contract`, `Open Design transport`, `implementation dispatcher`\n62: \n63: ```json\n64: {\"type\":\"claim-adjudication\",\"findingId\":\"SOL-A-I004-P1-001\",\"claim\":\"The phase-009 and phase-010 owning specs classify three existing runtime surfaces as creations even though the planned work is additive, leaving implementation routing contradictory.\",\"evidenceRefs\":[\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/009-foundations-motion/spec.md:99-104\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/009-foundations-motion/plan.md:97-105\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/009-foundations-motion/decision-record.md:125-131\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/010-open-design-transport/spec.md:83-88\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/010-open-design-transport/plan.md:91-97\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/010-open-design-transport/plan.md:143-146\",\".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/SKILL.md:1-15\",\".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/SKILL.md:1-15\",\".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-mcp-open-design/SKILL.md:1-18\"],\"counterevidenceSought\":\"Replayed affected-surface matrices, ADR implementation text, rollback semantics, requirements restricting changes to existing directories, and current owner contracts for proof that Create unambiguously meant additive files only.\",\"alternativeExplanation\":\"The ADRs and rollback plans repeatedly say proposed additions, and phase 010's plan says Add, strongly containing replacement risk; nevertheless, the owning action labels remain contradictory and phase 009 does not identify the additive file boundary.\",\"finalSeverity\":\"P1\",\"confidence\":0.8,\"downgradeTrigger\":\"Downgrade to P2 if dispatch is proven not to consume change-type labels and an authoritative affected-file manifest resolves every target to additive-only files while preserving current contracts.\"}\n65: ```\n66: \n67: ### P2 Findings\n68: None.\n69: \n70: ## Traceability Checks\n71: - `claim_replay`: partial — all five active P1 claims survived compact skeptic/referee replay at unchanged severity.\n72: - `producer_consumer`: partial — phase-004 hydration remains the shared producer for phase-006 STUDY, without root-containment acceptance criteria.\n73: - `negative_test_gap`: partial — phase-006 covers copied literals/spans but not behavioral instruction non-influence.\n74: - `metadata_consumer`: partial — stale continuity is contained by normal resume precedence but still exposed through canonical/no-redirect paths; empty dependencies suppress graph `blocks` links.\n75: - `change_classification`: partial — additive intent is documented, but the owning Create/Add labels remain contradictory.\n76: \n77: ## Integration Evidence\n78: - `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/quick_reference.md:492-498` names `/speckit:resume` phase-parent pointer/list behavior and confirms phase parents should not carry continuity blocks.\n79: - `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/resume/resume-ladder.ts:1000-1026` confirms child continuity is consumed from `implementation-summary.md` before spec-doc fallback.\n80: - `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/graph/graph-metadata-parser.ts:1712-1723` maps `manual.depends_on` into graph `blocks` links.\n81: - Current foundations, motion, and Open Design `SKILL.md` contracts prove the three phase-009/010 directory owners already exist.\n82: \n83: ## Edge Cases\n84: - Structural-impact analysis remained unavailable by detached-lineage design; direct reads and exact searches supplied graphless evidence.\n85: - Normal resume precedence contains, but does not erase, stale spec continuity; severity stayed P1 with a narrower consumer-impact statement.\n86: - Child-local dependency blockers are valid human-readable counterevidence, but do not populate graph consumers.\n87: - Additive ADR/rollback prose contains destructive intent; contradictory owning action labels still require reconciliation before dispatch.\n88: - No fixes have been applied, so every confirmed finding is `carried_forward`, never PASS.\n89: - Reducer placeholders `SUMMARY-P1-002`, `SUMMARY-P1-003`, and `SUMMARY-P1-004` are resolved as non-findings. The content-hash merge of `SOL-A-I003-P1-001` into `SOL-A-I001-P1-001` is a reducer warning only; both authoritative IDs are preserved because they are distinct claims sharing a parent-spec hash.\n90: \n91: ## Confirmed-Clean Surfaces\n92: - Phase-004 generation mismatch, rights, and corpus-change controls remain explicit; they do not substitute for path containment.\n93: - Phase-006 de-literalization, exact/span leak checks, reversibility, and no-STUDY retry remain valid controls; they do not test instruction non-influence.\n94: - Phase-007 fixes corpus and transport below user/mode/target authority.\n95: - Phase-009/010 ADR and rollback text clearly describe additive implementation intent, containing replacement risk.\n96: \n97: ## Ruled Out\n98: - Immediate child-resume misrouting from phase-002/003 stale spec continuity: ruled out by implementation-summary precedence.\n99: - Existing generation/rights tests as filesystem-containment proof: ruled out because they do not exercise traversal, symlinks, or canonical-root escape.\n100: - Literal/span leak gates as prompt-injection proof: ruled out because non-literal instruction following can pass both signals.\n101: - Child-local blockers as machine-readable graph projection: ruled out by the empty `manual.depends_on` arrays and graph parser mapping.\n102: - Destructive replacement as the stated phase-009/010 intent: ruled out by additive ADR and rollback language; the remaining finding is contradictory change classification.\n103: \n104: ## Next Focus\n105: - dimension: orchestrator-owned convergence decision\n106: - focus area: reduce stable replay state and evaluate synthesis eligibility\n107: - reason: all dimensions and the required stabilization replay are complete with zero new/refined findings and five unchanged P1s\n108: - rotation status: stabilization complete; no further LEAF dimension rotation required\n109: - blocked/productive carry-forward: do not retry exhausted inventories; preserve five authoritative IDs and three placeholder resolutions\n110: - required evidence: iteration-005 narrative, matching canonical delta/state record, and reducer-confirmed registry durability\n111: \n112: Review verdict: CONDITIONAL\n\n(End of file - total 112 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deep Review Iteration 005\n\n## Dispatcher\n- Route: `mode=review`, `target_agent=deep-review`, single YAML-owned LEAF iteration\n- Focus: cross-dimension stabilization and adversarial replay of all five authoritative P1 claims\n- Budget profile: `verify` (graphless direct-read, counterevidence, and consumer-impact replay)\n\n## Files Reviewed\n- Parent `spec.md` and `graph-metadata.json`; phase-002/003 specs and implementation summaries\n- Phase-004 retrieval spec/tasks/checklist; phase-006 STUDY spec/tasks/checklist; phase-007 authority seam\n- Phase-005–010 dependency declarations and child graph metadata\n- Phase-009/010 specs/plans plus current foundations, motion, and Open Design contracts\n- `system-spec-kit` continuity and graph-consumer contracts as named integration evidence only\n\n## Findings - New\nNo new finding IDs were created. The five authoritative P1s were replayed adversarially and remain active at the same severity.\n\n### P0 Findings\nNone.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/review/lineages/sol-a/iterations/iteration-005.md","text":"# Deep Review Iteration 005\n\n## Dispatcher\n- Route: `mode=review`, `target_agent=deep-review`, single YAML-owned LEAF iteration\n- Focus: cross-dimension stabilization and adversarial replay of all five authoritative P1 claims\n- Budget profile: `verify` (graphless direct-read, counterevidence, and consumer-impact replay)\n\n## Files Reviewed\n- Parent `spec.md` and `graph-metadata.json`; phase-002/003 specs and implementation summaries\n- Phase-004 retrieval spec/tasks/checklist; phase-006 STUDY spec/tasks/checklist; phase-007 authority seam\n- Phase-005–010 dependency declarations and child graph metadata\n- Phase-009/010 specs/plans plus current foundations, motion, and Open Design contracts\n- `system-spec-kit` continuity and graph-consumer contracts as named integration evidence only\n\n## Findings - New\nNo new finding IDs were created. The five authoritative P1s were replayed adversarially and remain active at the same severity.\n\n### P0 Findings\nNone.\n\n### P1 Findings\n1. **Completed research phases retain pre-run continuity state** -- `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/spec.md:13-25` -- The parent still says to run phase 001 at 0%, while its phase map marks 001-003 complete; phase-002/003 specs still say to dispatch completed research at 10% while their implementation summaries are complete at 100%. Resume prefers child implementation-summary continuity and a phase-parent pointer/list, which contains the immediate routing impact, but `--no-redirect` and canonical-doc fallback still expose the contradictory parent/spec state. The P1 therefore remains a required canonical-state repair rather than a blocker. [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/spec.md:13-25`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/spec.md:46`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/spec.md:13-30`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/implementation-summary.md:10-30`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/003-global-modes-utilization/spec.md:13-30`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/003-global-modes-utilization/implementation-summary.md:10-31`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/quick_reference.md:492-498`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/validation/template_compliance_contract.md:264`]\n   - Finding class: matrix/evidence\n   - Scope proof: Parent and all completed-child continuity surfaces were reread; phase-parent pointer/list behavior and child implementation-summary precedence were checked as counterevidence, but neither makes the contradictory canonical metadata accurate.\n   - Affected surface hints: `parent coordination snapshot`, `phase-002 resume fallback`, `phase-003 resume fallback`, `canonical packet retrieval`\n\n```json\n{\"type\":\"claim-adjudication\",\"findingId\":\"SOL-A-I001-P1-001\",\"claim\":\"Canonical packet surfaces give obsolete next actions and completion percentages for already-completed research phases.\",\"evidenceRefs\":[\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/spec.md:13-25\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/spec.md:46\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/spec.md:13-30\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/implementation-summary.md:10-30\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/003-global-modes-utilization/spec.md:13-30\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/003-global-modes-utilization/implementation-summary.md:10-31\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/quick_reference.md:492-498\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/validation/template_compliance_contract.md:264\"],\"counterevidenceSought\":\"Replayed child implementation-summary precedence, phase-parent pointer/list routing, null-pointer behavior, and --no-redirect canonical-doc exposure.\",\"alternativeExplanation\":\"Normal child resume consumes the complete implementation-summary continuity, and a parent resume with a null pointer lists children rather than obeying the stale parent next action; this contains immediate misrouting but does not remove contradictory canonical state or no-redirect/fallback exposure.\",\"finalSeverity\":\"P1\",\"confidence\":0.87,\"downgradeTrigger\":\"Downgrade to P2 only if every completion, indexing, no-redirect, and canonical-doc consumer is proven to suppress these spec continuity fields and the stale blocks are non-authoritative by contract.\"}\n```\n\n2. **Hydration has no contracted filesystem-containment boundary** -- `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/004-retrieval-substrate/spec.md:103-112` -- The hydration producer accepts manifest-selected artifacts and re-hashes them, but no requirement, task, checklist row, or negative fixture requires canonical-root containment, traversal rejection, or a symlink policy. Generation mismatch and rights controls are counterevidence for adjacent risks, not containment. Downstream STUDY hydration consumes this shared producer, so the missing negative boundary remains P1. [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/004-retrieval-substrate/spec.md:103-112`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/004-retrieval-substrate/spec.md:124-136`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/004-retrieval-substrate/spec.md:188-200`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/004-retrieval-substrate/tasks.md:106-112`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/004-retrieval-substrate/checklist.md:86-102`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/006-md-generator-study-exemplars/spec.md:73-79`]\n   - Finding class: class-of-bug\n   - Scope proof: Exact containment searches across the phase-004 owner found only canonical generation-input language and no realpath/traversal/symlink control; producer tasks and the security/fix matrix omit the corresponding negative tests.\n   - Affected surface hints: `manifest path producer`, `hydrate CLI`, `source-scan fallback`, `STUDY hydration consumer`\n\n```json\n{\"type\":\"claim-adjudication\",\"findingId\":\"SOL-A-I002-P1-001\",\"claim\":\"The phase-004 contract permits a conforming implementation to hydrate a corpus path that resolves outside the styles root because no containment or symlink invariant is specified.\",\"evidenceRefs\":[\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/004-retrieval-substrate/spec.md:103-112\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/004-retrieval-substrate/spec.md:124-136\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/004-retrieval-substrate/spec.md:188-200\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/004-retrieval-substrate/tasks.md:106-112\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/004-retrieval-substrate/checklist.md:86-102\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/006-md-generator-study-exemplars/spec.md:73-79\"],\"counterevidenceSought\":\"Searched the owner requirements, tasks, checklist, edge cases, and the STUDY consumer for realpath, canonical containment, traversal, symlink, root escape, and outside-root negative fixtures.\",\"alternativeExplanation\":\"Manifest-derived paths, generation re-hashing, and a future implementation may independently constrain reads; none is a binding root-containment invariant or negative test expectation.\",\"finalSeverity\":\"P1\",\"confidence\":0.93,\"downgradeTrigger\":\"Downgrade to P2 after immutable safe manifest paths, canonical root containment, explicit symlink policy, and negative traversal/escape fixtures become binding acceptance criteria.\"}\n```\n\n3. **The STUDY injection envelope records a boundary but does not neutralize untrusted instructions** -- `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/006-md-generator-study-exemplars/spec.md:104-117` -- Phase 006 injects transformed corpus observations into the prompt and checks literal/span leakage at the authored-draft boundary, but it has no closed data-only schema, imperative/instruction rejection, or behavioral non-influence fixture. The phase-007 authority order prevents corpus evidence from becoming authority but does not sanitize the prompt content. The prompt producer and `runGuided` retry consumer can therefore pass every specified leak test while following a non-literal corpus instruction. [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/006-md-generator-study-exemplars/spec.md:73-79`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/006-md-generator-study-exemplars/spec.md:104-117`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/006-md-generator-study-exemplars/spec.md:165-187`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/006-md-generator-study-exemplars/tasks.md:65-80`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/006-md-generator-study-exemplars/checklist.md:96-118`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/007-shared-context-seam/spec.md:99-111`]\n   - Finding class: cross-consumer\n   - Scope proof: Exact prompt-injection counterevidence search found only the finding-class label; direct producer/consumer replay covered transformer, prompt builder, plan builder, authored-draft gate, retry, fixture matrix, and shared authority ordering.\n   - Affected surface hints: `study transformer`, `STUDY prompt block`, `buildWritePrompt/buildPlan`, `runGuided retry`, `behavioral fixtures`\n\n```json\n{\"type\":\"claim-adjudication\",\"findingId\":\"SOL-A-I002-P1-002\",\"claim\":\"The planned phase-006 controls can pass while corpus-borne instructions influence generated prose, because the envelope is metadata and the leak gate only tests copied values/spans.\",\"evidenceRefs\":[\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/006-md-generator-study-exemplars/spec.md:73-79\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/006-md-generator-study-exemplars/spec.md:104-117\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/006-md-generator-study-exemplars/spec.md:165-187\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/006-md-generator-study-exemplars/tasks.md:65-80\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/006-md-generator-study-exemplars/checklist.md:96-118\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/007-shared-context-seam/spec.md:99-111\"],\"counterevidenceSought\":\"Searched requirements, tasks, checklist, fixtures, and shared authority controls for prompt injection, untrusted instructions, imperative rejection, data-only parsing, sanitization, and behavioral non-influence tests.\",\"alternativeExplanation\":\"A strict de-literalizing transformer and fixed authority order could incidentally discard imperatives, but neither requires instruction rejection and the exact/span leak signals cannot detect non-literal instruction following.\",\"finalSeverity\":\"P1\",\"confidence\":0.92,\"downgradeTrigger\":\"Downgrade to P2 if the transformer becomes a closed data-only schema with explicit instruction rejection and adversarial behavioral non-influence fixtures across prompt and draft consumers.\"}\n```\n\n4. **Canonical parent surfaces omit the implementation-phase dependency graph** -- `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/spec.md:121-126` -- The parent handoff table records only the research-to-implementation transition, while phase-005–010 docs declare blocking prerequisites and all child `manual.depends_on` arrays remain empty. The graph parser converts `depends_on` into `blocks` causal links, so empty arrays remove these edges from graph/index consumers even though child-local tasks contain human-readable blockers. Child-local controls limit immediate risk but do not give orchestration and memory consumers a canonical dependency projection. [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/spec.md:121-126`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/graph-metadata.json:6-21`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/005-md-generator-schema-contract/spec.md:143-150`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/006-md-generator-study-exemplars/tasks.md:56-70`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/007-shared-context-seam/spec.md:128-135`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/009-foundations-motion/spec.md:143-150`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/010-open-design-transport/spec.md:125-135`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/graph/graph-metadata-parser.ts:1712-1723`]\n   - Finding class: matrix/evidence\n   - Scope proof: Exact dependency replay covered the parent handoff, every phase-004–010 graph file, child-local blocking declarations, and the system graph consumer that maps `depends_on` to `blocks` links.\n   - Affected surface hints: `parent phase map`, `child graph metadata`, `causal graph blocks`, `resume/planning context`\n\n```json\n{\"type\":\"claim-adjudication\",\"findingId\":\"SOL-A-I003-P1-001\",\"claim\":\"The canonical parent and graph metadata cannot represent or surface the implementation-phase ordering that child packets require.\",\"evidenceRefs\":[\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/spec.md:121-126\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/graph-metadata.json:6-21\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/005-md-generator-schema-contract/spec.md:143-150\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/006-md-generator-study-exemplars/tasks.md:56-70\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/007-shared-context-seam/spec.md:128-135\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/009-foundations-motion/spec.md:143-150\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/010-open-design-transport/spec.md:125-135\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/graph/graph-metadata-parser.ts:1712-1723\"],\"counterevidenceSought\":\"Reviewed child dependency tables and blocked tasks, parent transition rules, every planned-child graph field, and the graph parser for proof that child-local prose alone is the canonical machine-consumed ordering source.\",\"alternativeExplanation\":\"Child-local blocked tasks encode ordering for a human implementer and all phases remain planned; however, graph consumers map only populated manual.depends_on fields into blocks links, so the canonical machine surface still omits the relationships.\",\"finalSeverity\":\"P1\",\"confidence\":0.86,\"downgradeTrigger\":\"Downgrade to P2 if the owning workflow proves child-local blockers are the sole validated ordering authority and graph blocks are explicitly non-orchestrational/non-retrieval metadata.\"}\n```\n\n5. **Two implementation packets classify existing mode and transport surfaces as new creations** -- `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/009-foundations-motion/spec.md:99-104` -- Phase 009 labels existing foundations and motion directory globs `Create` in both spec and plan, while phase 010's spec labels its existing transport directory `Create` and its plan says `Add`. The plans, rollback text, and ADRs repeatedly say “additions,” which is substantial counterevidence against destructive replacement and prevents escalation; however, the authoritative affected-surface action labels still contradict the current owners and leave additive file boundaries unnamed. This remains a P1 spec mismatch to resolve before implementation dispatch. [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/009-foundations-motion/spec.md:99-104`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/009-foundations-motion/plan.md:97-105`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/009-foundations-motion/decision-record.md:125-131`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/010-open-design-transport/spec.md:83-88`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/010-open-design-transport/plan.md:91-97`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/010-open-design-transport/plan.md:143-146`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/SKILL.md:1-15`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/SKILL.md:1-15`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-mcp-open-design/SKILL.md:1-18`]\n   - Finding class: matrix/evidence\n   - Scope proof: Action-label search covered phase-004–010; direct reads prove all three directory owners already exist, while phase-009 ADR/plan and phase-010 plan/rollback prove intended semantics are additive but do not reconcile the owning labels.\n   - Affected surface hints: `design-foundations contract`, `design-motion contract`, `Open Design transport`, `implementation dispatcher`\n\n```json\n{\"type\":\"claim-adjudication\",\"findingId\":\"SOL-A-I004-P1-001\",\"claim\":\"The phase-009 and phase-010 owning specs classify three existing runtime surfaces as creations even though the planned work is additive, leaving implementation routing contradictory.\",\"evidenceRefs\":[\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/009-foundations-motion/spec.md:99-104\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/009-foundations-motion/plan.md:97-105\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/009-foundations-motion/decision-record.md:125-131\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/010-open-design-transport/spec.md:83-88\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/010-open-design-transport/plan.md:91-97\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/010-open-design-transport/plan.md:143-146\",\".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/SKILL.md:1-15\",\".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/SKILL.md:1-15\",\".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-mcp-open-design/SKILL.md:1-18\"],\"counterevidenceSought\":\"Replayed affected-surface matrices, ADR implementation text, rollback semantics, requirements restricting changes to existing directories, and current owner contracts for proof that Create unambiguously meant additive files only.\",\"alternativeExplanation\":\"The ADRs and rollback plans repeatedly say proposed additions, and phase 010's plan says Add, strongly containing replacement risk; nevertheless, the owning action labels remain contradictory and phase 009 does not identify the additive file boundary.\",\"finalSeverity\":\"P1\",\"confidence\":0.8,\"downgradeTrigger\":\"Downgrade to P2 if dispatch is proven not to consume change-type labels and an authoritative affected-file manifest resolves every target to additive-only files while preserving current contracts.\"}\n```\n\n### P2 Findings\nNone.\n\n## Traceability Checks\n- `claim_replay`: partial — all five active P1 claims survived compact skeptic/referee replay at unchanged severity.\n- `producer_consumer`: partial — phase-004 hydration remains the shared producer for phase-006 STUDY, without root-containment acceptance criteria.\n- `negative_test_gap`: partial — phase-006 covers copied literals/spans but not behavioral instruction non-influence.\n- `metadata_consumer`: partial — stale continuity is contained by normal resume precedence but still exposed through canonical/no-redirect paths; empty dependencies suppress graph `blocks` links.\n- `change_classification`: partial — additive intent is documented, but the owning Create/Add labels remain contradictory.\n\n## Integration Evidence\n- `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/quick_reference.md:492-498` names `/speckit:resume` phase-parent pointer/list behavior and confirms phase parents should not carry continuity blocks.\n- `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/resume/resume-ladder.ts:1000-1026` confirms child continuity is consumed from `implementation-summary.md` before spec-doc fallback.\n- `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/graph/graph-metadata-parser.ts:1712-1723` maps `manual.depends_on` into graph `blocks` links.\n- Current foundations, motion, and Open Design `SKILL.md` contracts prove the three phase-009/010 directory owners already exist.\n\n## Edge Cases\n- Structural-impact analysis remained unavailable by detached-lineage design; direct reads and exact searches supplied graphless evidence.\n- Normal resume precedence contains, but does not erase, stale spec continuity; severity stayed P1 with a narrower consumer-impact statement.\n- Child-local dependency blockers are valid human-readable counterevidence, but do not populate graph consumers.\n- Additive ADR/rollback prose contains destructive intent; contradictory owning action labels still require reconciliation before dispatch.\n- No fixes have been applied, so every confirmed finding is `carried_forward`, never PASS.\n- Reducer placeholders `SUMMARY-P1-002`, `SUMMARY-P1-003`, and `SUMMARY-P1-004` are resolved as non-findings. The content-hash merge of `SOL-A-I003-P1-001` into `SOL-A-I001-P1-001` is a reducer warning only; both authoritative IDs are preserved because they are distinct claims sharing a parent-spec hash.\n\n## Confirmed-Clean Surfaces\n- Phase-004 generation mismatch, rights, and corpus-change controls remain explicit; they do not substitute for path containment.\n- Phase-006 de-literalization, exact/span leak checks, reversibility, and no-STUDY retry remain valid controls; they do not test instruction non-influence.\n- Phase-007 fixes corpus and transport below user/mode/target authority.\n- Phase-009/010 ADR and rollback text clearly describe additive implementation intent, containing replacement risk.\n\n## Ruled Out\n- Immediate child-resume misrouting from phase-002/003 stale spec continuity: ruled out by implementation-summary precedence.\n- Existing generation/rights tests as filesystem-containment proof: ruled out because they do not exercise traversal, symlinks, or canonical-root escape.\n- Literal/span leak gates as prompt-injection proof: ruled out because non-literal instruction following can pass both signals.\n- Child-local blockers as machine-readable graph projection: ruled out by the empty `manual.depends_on` arrays and graph parser mapping.\n- Destructive replacement as the stated phase-009/010 intent: ruled out by additive ADR and rollback language; the remaining finding is contradictory change classification.\n\n## Next Focus\n- dimension: orchestrator-owned convergence decision\n- focus area: reduce stable replay state and evaluate synthesis eligibility\n- reason: all dimensions and the required stabilization replay are complete with zero new/refined findings and five unchanged P1s\n- rotation status: stabilization complete; no further LEAF dimension rotation required\n- blocked/productive carry-forward: do not retry exhausted inventories; preserve five authoritative IDs and three placeholder resolutions\n- required evidence: iteration-005 narrative, matching canonical delta/state record, and reducer-confirmed registry durability\n\nReview verdict: CONDITIONAL","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":112,"totalLines":112,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/review/lineages/sol-a/iterations/iteration-005.md","time":{"start":1784389911765,"end":1784389911772}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f5140b5963ca347016a5ba1174f248191883ff80c52f57389"}},"id":"prt_f75ed440c001T82q7FE7xHNbrX","sessionID":"ses_08a55b97affezjS590Sxu4oUZ9","messageID":"msg_f75ed1160001SgtmDLCQn9U23u"}}
