-sk-design-styles-utilization/004-retrieval-substrate/spec.md:124-136\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/004-retrieval-substrate/spec.md:188-200\"],\"counterevidenceSought\":\"Searched phase-004/006/007/010 artifacts for realpath, canonicalization, traversal, root confinement, and symlink controls.\",\"alternativeExplanation\":\"Implementation may independently enforce containment, but neither containment nor fixed safe path generation is an acceptance criterion.\",\"finalSeverity\":\"P1\",\"confidence\":0.9,\"downgradeTrigger\":\"Downgrade to P2 if immutable manifest paths, canonical containment, symlink policy, and negative traversal fixtures become required.\"}},{\"id\":\"SOL-A-I002-P1-002\",\"severity\":\"P1\",\"category\":\"security\",\"dimension\":\"security\",\"status\":\"carried\",\"title\":\"The STUDY injection envelope records a boundary but does not neutralize untrusted instructions\",\"file\":\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/006-md-generator-study-exemplars/spec.md:104-117\",\"evidence\":\"The planned transformer injects corpus observations but specifies no data-only parsing, instruction rejection, or behavioral non-influence fixture.\",\"findingClass\":\"cross-consumer\",\"scopeProof\":\"Phase-006 artifacts repeat the envelope but lack prompt-injection behavior criteria; phase-007 authority ordering does not sanitize content.\",\"affectedSurfaceHints\":[\"study transformer\",\"STUDY prompt block\",\"adversarial fixtures\",\"runGuided retry\"],\"content_hash\":\"5d2be1beddf22032bde4e59d4bb0d4b73c7f3a54d1718ede78e6988f0c7918aa\",\"claimAdjudication\":{\"type\":\"claim-adjudication\",\"findingId\":\"SOL-A-I002-P1-002\",\"claim\":\"The planned phase-006 controls can pass while corpus-borne instructions influence generated prose, because the envelope is metadata and the leak gate only tests copied values/spans.\",\"evidenceRefs\":[\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/006-md-generator-study-exemplars/spec.md:73-79\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/006-md-generator-study-exemplars/spec.md:104-117\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/006-md-generator-study-exemplars/spec.md:165-187\"],\"counterevidenceSought\":\"Searched planning artifacts for prompt injection, untrusted content, instruction rejection, sanitization, and injection-boundary controls.\",\"alternativeExplanation\":\"A strict transformer could incidentally discard imperatives, but current criteria do not require that property and leak signals do not detect non-literal instruction following.\",\"finalSeverity\":\"P1\",\"confidence\":0.88,\"downgradeTrigger\":\"Downgrade to P2 if the transformer becomes a closed data-only schema with instruction rejection and behavioral fixtures.\"}},{\"id\":\"SOL-A-I003-P1-001\",\"severity\":\"P1\",\"category\":\"traceability\",\"dimension\":\"traceability\",\"status\":\"carried\",\"title\":\"Canonical parent surfaces omit the implementation-phase dependency graph\",\"file\":\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/spec.md:121-126\",\"evidence\":\"Child packets declare eleven implementation dependency edges, but the parent handoff table and all planned child graph dependency arrays omit them.\",\"findingClass\":\"matrix/evidence\",\"scopeProof\":\"Dependency searches covered the parent and every phase-004-010 child planning and graph surface.\",\"affectedSurfaceHints\":[\"parent phase map\",\"child graph metadata\",\"resume routing\",\"dependency gate validation\"],\"content_hash\":\"c573671842aef0aa61fb93e6b7d0c7a43fc1f1320f1e48a356adfa6db64a50fd\",\"claimAdjudication\":{\"type\":\"claim-adjudication\",\"findingId\":\"SOL-A-I003-P1-001\",\"claim\":\"The canonical parent and graph metadata cannot represent or validate the implementation-phase ordering that child packets require.\",\"evidenceRefs\":[\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/spec.md:121-126\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/graph-metadata.json:6-21\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/005-md-generator-schema-contract/spec.md:143-150\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/007-shared-context-seam/spec.md:128-135\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/010-open-design-transport/spec.md:125-135\"],\"counterevidenceSought\":\"Reviewed child dependency tables, blocked tasks, predecessor/successor references, parent transition rules, and all phase-004-010 graph fields.\",\"alternativeExplanation\":\"Child-local blockers encode ordering and limit immediate risk, but do not populate canonical parent or machine-readable graph surfaces.\",\"finalSeverity\":\"P1\",\"confidence\":0.9,\"downgradeTrigger\":\"Downgrade to P2 if graph dependencies are proven unrelated to child sequencing and child blockers are the sole validated authority.\"}},{\"id\":\"SOL-A-I004-P1-001\",\"severity\":\"P1\",\"category\":\"maintainability\",\"dimension\":\"maintainability\",\"status\":\"new\",\"title\":\"Two implementation packets classify existing mode and transport surfaces as new creations\",\"file\":\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/009-foundations-motion/spec.md:99-104\",\"evidence\":\"Phase 009 marks existing foundations and motion contracts as Create in spec and plan; phase 010's spec marks the existing transport directory Create while its plan says Add.\",\"findingClass\":\"matrix/evidence\",\"scopeProof\":\"Exact change-type searches covered phase-004-010 artifacts and direct reads proved all three runtime contracts already exist.\",\"affectedSurfaceHints\":[\"design-foundations contract\",\"design-motion contract\",\"Open Design transport\",\"phase implementation routing\"],\"content_hash\":\"b7cf0020db168dabf10e64564a8d5ffba7c8ef4299f5cd37ea364573d500cb45\",\"claimAdjudication\":{\"type\":\"claim-adjudication\",\"findingId\":\"SOL-A-I004-P1-001\",\